content: I got this app because I lost my Set cards. I love that it tells you if the set was right. The hint option is super useful for times when we can't find a set. I wish it had an option to automatically track the score for multiple players to make it like the original "family game". When we played, I kept score on a piece of paper which meant I was slower to find sets because I had to look away from the screen each time to track scores.

Alright game, but there's a pretty annoying bug where if you have the "guaranteed set" option enabled, you can still be dealt a board with no set in place if the three cards being drawn are the last in the draw pile. In that case, you have to hit the no set button, at which point the game will end.
Great, just difficult when tired. Also it doesn't seem to recognise that I have a tablet too, mis-sync?
Great compliment to the physical SET Card Game. I love the puzzle and classic mode. Please create online competition mode.
Great app! If you like the card version of SET, you will love playing on the app.
Fun game, but if I paid, isn't it wrong of you to clutter my experience with ads?
Very occasional ad popup. Not glitchy. I love set in real life and this does it justice
i paid for this and I still get ads? not right at all!
would like to be able to shuffle the cards

UPDATE: The developer contacted me and said they will look into the possibility of adding an option to turn off the timer. His response was polite and very helpful, so I changed my review from 1 to 4 stars. When I tried to play this game (classic mode, by myself), there was some kind of timer/ticker going at the bottom of the screen. It kept going the whole time I was playing, and it was so distracting that I stopped before the game was over. I couldn't find a way to turn that off, so I sent an email to the developer. They didn't respond, so I requested a refund. Google Play declined my request. Now I am stuck with a game that I don't even want to play because that timer (which has no relevance to the game) won't stop. Most games I have that have timers include an option to turn them off.
why are there ads in a paid app? its set and thats great but cmon guys
replyContent: You are correct, there are ads in the app.  However, they are very infrequent and only show up upon completion of a game (they never interrupt a game).  It is not a paid ad service, the ads are included only to let our digital audience know about the card and board games from Set Enterprises. We really appreciate the feedback though.

content: SET is a great game to enhance pattern recognition skills and this app is a well-designed version for both play and training purposes. It gives you lots of options, too. One warning: it's addicting.
This is my favorite card game - I'm so happy I can play it on my phone now!!!!! The marathon version is really addictive!
Finally an official SET app! I can't stop playing!
I love this game! We have played the card game for years in our family. Now it's on my phone and it has so many different ways to play! So excited!!!
